               <p>JOSEPH WILLIAM HORNBY. I live in Great Cambridge-street, Hackney-road. On the 19th of February, about seven o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18310407-221-crimeloc1190">Old-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-221-crimeloc1190" type="placeName" value="Old-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-221-crimeloc1190" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-221-off1188 t18310407-221-crimeloc1190"></join>, going into the City - I wanted to use my handkerchief, and on feeling in my pocket it was gone; while I was feeling for it an officer came up, and asked if I had lost any thing - he went about fifteen yards forward, and caught the prisoner, brought him back, and said, "This is the boy who picked your pocket, I saw him;" somebody in the crowd told him not to be afraid - he said, "I have done nothing, what have I to be afraid of?" my handkerchief has not been found.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-221-person1581">
                  GEORGE 
                  KEMP
               <interp inst="t18310407-221-person1581" type="surname" value="KEMP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-221-person1581" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-221-person1581" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. On the 19th of February, I saw Mr. Hornby near the London Apprentice- I saw the prisoner in company with another boy, lay hold of Mr. Hornby's coat pocket; I was in plain clothes - he turned round, saw me, and I suppose knew me, for he let go of it; I crossed over to the other side, saw him following Mr. Hornby, watched him, and near the City-road, I saw the prisoner put his hand into the pocket, take the handkerchief out, and give it to the other, who ran away with it directly - I informed Mr. Hornby, and fetched the prisoner back, without losing sight of him; I had seen him before - I think I should know the other lad.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310407-221-verdict1191" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310407-221-verdict1191" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14. - <rs id="t18310407-221-punish1192" type="punishmentDescription">
